HEADWORD: Gainage
<hw>Gain"age</hw> <pr>(?, 48)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>gaignage</ets> pasturage, crop, F. <ets>gaignage</ets> pasturage.
See <er>Gain</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The horses, oxen, plows, wains or wagons and
implements for carrying on tillage.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The profit
made by tillage; also, the land itself.</def>
<rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
